narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it. Even if you're done with your language credits this class is enjoyable, pretty easy, and a great way to get closer to Marta who gladly writes recommendations to anything.

If you need this class for distributional requirements or credit, take it. It's not the best class as far as material and teaching is concerned. But you get to read an entire 350 page book in Portuguese and you get a credit and a half.
Practice makes perfect. This class is a great opportunity to improve your language skills in portuguese by speaking a lot every day.
It's an easy credit, but your Portuguese is not going to get much better.
Yes, Marta is a very patient teacher and you will learn a lot.
